	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>RE: Actually...</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Fri, Jan 3rd 4:39 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=168045><span id= >Zaendol</span></a><br><span id=notbold>13 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Umm...<br><br>Don't mean this as a flame, but anyone who says getting the 8th shawl is 'such an easy quest', has not done it themselves I would gather.&nbsp;&nbsp;Maybe you are meaning only this last fight, but that has nothing to do with how difficult this quest is.  This quest is quite an undertaking, and if you have gotten tailoring and smithing to 162 and 190 respectively, you will know what I mean.  And that is only a fraction of the work required.  It is a bit easier these days with the bazaar, and how you can buy the tradeskill items there, and cut the time down substantially, but it is still a serious hit to the pocketbook as well.  There is no way you can call this an easy quest.  I am up to the 8th shawl, and have been working on it since lvl 35...  It has been the most time-consuming frustrating thing I have ever done in EQ by far!!  hehe.<br><br>The guild I'm in has only a couple of people with the 8th shawl, and they are very proud of it, whereas we farm NToV and the rest of the Velious/Luclin loot circuit, and those drops are common in the guild, and only require raid participation to aquire....  And these places are raided on a daily basis, whereas 8th shawl quest events are a rarity.  Items like these would never go to twinks, I guarantee that.  There are plenty of people who could use them.<br><br><br>Just making sure people are not misled here.<br><br>Zaendol Tohvars<br>62nd Wizard of Solusek Ro<br>Drinal<br></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
